That's not entirely true.  I've seen other RP environments (MUSHes) where RP died not because everyone stopped RPing but because people refused to accept a central set of guidelines.  Instead they all clamored for &quot;consensual role-playing&quot; but since they then began using &quot;consensus&quot; to refuse to RP with people outside their little cliques RP on the MUSH broke down into a series of camps only RPing amonst themselves.  New players could not get involved and the entire place ended up dying in a bitter nasty way.<br>
