<br>
And yes, taking away the alignments did contribute to the decline of roleplaying in general. People didn't have the option to choose NOT to roleplay alignments. It was the closest thing to enforced roleplay I've seen. Take that away, and you get paladins grouping with necromancers.<br>
<br>
Good roleplayers will roleplay anywhere, anytime. They came here because Sony initially made it a place where the rules made it difficult for lazy roleplayers and non-roleplayers destroy the immersive environment. Then they took those rules away.<br>
<br>
Yes, we could roleplay in the middle of the local mall if we really wanted to. But why would we want to? People aren't saying that their personal roleplay skills suddenly disappeared. They're bemoaning the fact that Sony built a mall on top of our medieval town and we're still trying to live in it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kazot>Kazot</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Your powers are useless<br>
The clowns are on my side</span><br>  Posts: 45<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/19/03 12:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3873.topic&index=39>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Does -anyone- believe RP is as alive on FV as it used to</span><hr size=1> Every one who plays EQ role-plays to some extent. Lets face it you don’t see many regular people running around battling dragons and using magic.<br>
<br>
Some people casually play a character letting RL come and go with out a really bothering to notice, others play their character in very strict constraints and they don’t want any mention of RL and a third group denies they RP while casting spells and wielding magic weapons as if it were normal. <br>
<br>
That said, it is more a matter of how much each person chooses to RP and to what extent they think everyone else should have to RP back at them.<br>
<br>
Titaisia once spoke about the Captain Kirk Scenario, this would be RP. Even if it didn’t fit many others requirements it would still be RP and it could be very well done by the right person. <br>
<br>
I see more complaining about other peoples RP than I see people focusing on what they doing to encourage RP and interaction.<br>
<br>
As for Epic or Grand RP scenarios, I think they are still possible. It is just having the person or people who are willing to put in the time and effort to make it all happen that’s keeps it from being more common.<br>
<br>
So In my opinion there is a ton of RP at all levels. You just have to look around and see it instead of looking for the absence of what you want it to be.<br>
