My definition of playing a role-playing game includes playing within the confines of the setting environment.  If yours doesn't then you are not somebody I want to role-play with.  My problem is that the population of people who either:<br>
a) don't want to role-play<br>
b) role-play but ignore the confines of the setting environment or<br>
c) role-play but have no idea what FV's setting environment was defined as<br>
<br>
...has reached such a level that role-playing on FV is not possible for me.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>So In my opinion there is a ton of RP at all levels. You just have to look around and see it instead of looking for the absence of what you want it to be.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
